values: I'm finally writing my journal again cause I know you all love to read it.  Baseball camp was awsome, even though it rained practically everyday.  Trevor and Scott were too funny.  I did more whiffle ball and basketball at baseball camp than I did baseball.  One night a coach walked in to make sure we were asleep, and I was as usually spazing in my sleep and he came up to me cause I was talking and I smacked him so he punched me and woke me up.  Too bad I can't go back next year.  Over these past two days I've done nothing so there you go

hokay. So the last few days have ben the worst this summer at least funwise.  I've been so bored it sucks.  I saw Napolean Dynomite on Monday with Doug Brandon and John, I will kill doug and john for dragging me into that gay movie.  IT SUCKED!!!  There was no plot line to it,  no point to the movie It must have been made by a group of computer nerds who had alot of money and way too much free time.  Then on the way home John blasted Nelly and screamed stuff out the window to people.  It was quite funny.  Yesterday I did absoloutly nothing except for video games and basketball.  HOPEFULLY today will be better but as of now there seems no such luck.
I Love you Ashley Blair

I haven't written in the past few days.  I don't know what to say about the last few days except for they've been fun.  I am bored at this moment.  Over the past few days I've been trying to beat the game Splinter Cell Pandora Tomorrow.  That game is hard to beat it takes like 20 frickin trys until eventually I throw the controler across the room in anger.  Wednesday I went to charlie's he got us all in trouble that idiot.  Then I went to Doug's on thursday.  Friday I went to the movies and the mall with Nick it was ok could  have been better.  Yesterday i had my family graduation party.  It was fun always great to see my cousins funny kids I must say.  Today I am doing nothing as of now as I said earlier.  I want to go to great adventure some time next weak and have it not get screwed up. bye bye.  I love you Ashley

Ya I am bored as of now and this is the onyl thing to do.  Also my journal seems a topic of alot of contraversy so I'll try and not put anything offensive or whatever in it.  I saw dodgeball again yesterday.  That movie has to be one ot the greatest movies of all time. and if you disagree than you're wrong.  While we are on the topic of the boxoffice  I have the displeasure of hearing more bullshlong about the hippie liberal propaganda movie Ferenhiet 9/11.  It was proven that over 85% of that movie is Fiction and only 10% is true the other 5% is unknown.  So if you are so cynical and stupid to believe the word of a lowly educated 350 pound fat man ( and no I don't mean budda) then you can waste $8 and 2 hours of you life to see something that almost makes me laugh at it's random assumptions and irelevant talk.  Now back to what most of you all care about MY LIFE!  By the way doug thanks for breaking my cell phone I love you. My band seems to be going slower than a slug stuck in molasis. But I have started writing lyrics.  Today I am going to Charlie's to hang with all my G's this should be fun.  by the way if you would like to visit the best and funniest site on the internet go to www.maddox.xmission.com  please if you are going to eb offended by volgar language and sexaul/racial  comments than please don't visit this site.  But if you like to laugh at yourself and others than please visit for a good laugh.   now it's time to end it up.  I love you Ashley Taylor Blair

WOW!!! How would I explain these past few days.  Too many memories in this summer so far to contain.  In 7 days of summer this summer has already beaten past ones. Doug pulled a funny. I mena who goes to Great Adventure and right at the gate says " I forgot my pass"  well the Great Adventure story is very long and in detail so I don't feel like writing it. By the way Thank you for coming Brandon.( not)  Then last night was too great to explain on this page.  Just me and the girl I love hiding from Kristina Doug and Chaz aka Chuckie aka clay aka Charlie as we played manhunt.  I chose some good spots so me and Ash could just have some time alone to talk.  They gave up looking for us after 5 minutes.  Then ya it was AWSOME.  I  LOVE YOU ASHLEY TAYLOR BLAIR.

Well on Tuesday I saw Dodgeball. It was hilarious I'd see it again if I got the chance to.  Then I went to the mall and got some new shirts.  Then we all went becak to charlie's house for no reason.  Then Yesterday me and Mike and Chris and Nick hung out we acted liek idiots. Me and Mike were like the onyl kids not at dara's party.  I want my band to get together on Monday to practice so we don't like die out on the whole thing. Today I had a party for baseball it was fun just me John and Stevey. Right now I'm bored. I want to do somethign tonight but I can safely bet $1,000 dollars that no one will be able to. so What else is new.

<FONT color=#cc6600>Finally I am through with the torture of Middle school.  I hate all the teachers they all were annoying.  Graduation was boring and hottt!!!!  I was sweating my balls off out there.Tony's friend brightened up the whole ceremony with his comment.HAHAHA! Finally tomorrow starts my favorite time of all, SUMMER!  But I have to live 3 days without the love of my life Ashley because she's away. How will I do it!!!  I LOVE HER SO MUCH!!!!!</FONT>

<FONT color=#330099>Today was boring at first. At church for once I didn't fall asleep because the new priest is cool.  Then I sat home for like 4 hours. I had to pass up almost 4 offers to do something because my mom wouldn't have let me go, because I was going to my aunt's for Father's day at 4.  When I went to my cousin's it was cool. Alex did  a huge back flop off the diving board.  Then we played some baseball. They think I'm going to be the next Roger Clemens ( obviously they don't watch or play alot of baseball).  Then we played basketball, I stuffed my cousin's 6 times. Alex thinks my band should do a cover of Slipnot, (he has no taste in music)  I just laughed. Then he was tryign to give me love advice.  Don't worry I think Ashley can account for me when I say I know how to love. </FONT><FONT color=#ff0000>I love you Ashley</FONT>

Incased you haven't noticed, or you have a slowly processing brain, I really don't care about Graduation.  I hated Middle School it sucked, but I have to admit it wasn't as bad as my old school (let's not get into that).  Can you believe today I wore an Adopt a Beach shirt. I must be the only Republican in the world to ever do that.  I'm trying to write some music for my band but it is hard.  Almost every phrase I write is already in a song!!!( or it's just gay).  And just for the record I love Ashley Taylor Blair
